# 🍳 Find My Recipes – Frontend

## Description

This frontend of the "Find My Recipes" application — a responsive web interface for discovering recipes based on ingredients you already have at home. This user-friendly application helps users find recipes with food they already have, this is designed to be a qucik and easy use tool to make home cooked meals without having to go to the store.

## 🔍 Features

- 🔎 **Search**: Enter ingredients and discover relevant recipes.
- 📝 **Recipe Details**: View instructions, prep time, and nutrition info.
- //❤️ **Favorites**: Save your favorite recipes for easy access later.
- 🌐 **API Integration**: Communicates with personlized backend.

## 🛠️ Built With

- **React**
- **JavaScript**
- **Styled with CSS / CSS Modules**
- **Fetch API** for API requests

## 📦 Getting Started

1.  **Clone the repository:**

````bash
git clone https://github.com/rmhockey10/Capstone.FindMyRecipe.Frontend
cd Capstone.FindMyRecipe.Frontend
npm install
npm start


### Installation & Setup
1.  **Clone the repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone <https://github.com/rmhockey10/Capstone.FindMyRecipe.Backend.git>
    cd Capstone.FindMyRecipe.Backend
    ```
2.  **Install :**
    ```bash
    npm install
    ```

3.  **Project structure :**
    src/
├── api/
├── auth/
├── images/
├── layout/
├── recipes/
├── App.jsx/
├── Error404.jsx/
├── FindMyRecipeContext.jsx/
└── index.css



